Here's the standard approach:

### 1. Define each theme as a `ResourceDictionary`

Create three XAML files (e.g., in a `Themes/` folder):

```xml
<!-- Themes/LightTheme.xaml -->
<ResourceDictionary xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui"
                    xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml"
                    x:Class="MyApp.Themes.LightTheme">
    <Color x:Key="PageBackground">#FFFFFF</Color>
    <Color x:Key="TextPrimary">#1A1A1A</Color>
    <Color x:Key="AccentColor">#0078D4</Color>
    <!-- … -->
</ResourceDictionary>
```

Repeat for `DarkTheme.xaml` and `HighContrastTheme.xaml` with the same keys but different values.

### 2. Add a theme-switching helper

```csharp
public enum AppTheme { Light, Dark, HighContrast }

public static class ThemeManager
{
    public static void ApplyTheme(AppTheme theme)
    {
        var mergedDicts = Application.Current!.Resources.MergedDictionaries;
        mergedDicts.Clear();

        mergedDicts.Add(theme switch
        {
            AppTheme.Dark         => new Themes.DarkTheme(),
            AppTheme.HighContrast => new Themes.HighContrastTheme(),
            _                     => new Themes.LightTheme(),
        });

        // Persist the choice
        Preferences.Set("app_theme", theme.ToString());
    }

    public static AppTheme LoadSavedTheme()
    {
        var saved = Preferences.Get("app_theme", nameof(AppTheme.Light));
        return Enum.TryParse<AppTheme>(saved, out var t) ? t : AppTheme.Light;
    }
}
```

### 3. Apply the saved theme at startup

In `App.xaml.cs`:

```csharp
public App()
{
    InitializeComponent();
    ThemeManager.ApplyTheme(ThemeManager.LoadSavedTheme());
}
```

### 4. Build the settings page

```xml
<Picker Title="Theme" x:Name="ThemePicker"
        ItemsSource="{Binding Themes}"
        SelectedItem="{Binding SelectedTheme}"
        SelectedIndexChanged="OnThemeChanged" />
```

```csharp
void OnThemeChanged(object? sender, EventArgs e)
{
    if (ThemePicker.SelectedItem is AppTheme theme)
        ThemeManager.ApplyTheme(theme);
}
```

### 5. Consume theme colors via `DynamicResource`

Use `DynamicResource` (not `StaticResource`) so controls update immediately when the dictionary changes:

```xml
<Label Text="Hello" TextColor="{DynamicResource TextPrimary}" />
<ContentPage BackgroundColor="{DynamicResource PageBackground}">
```

**Key points:**
- Same keys in every theme dictionary — only values differ.
- `DynamicResource` makes the swap instant; `StaticResource` won't update.
- `Preferences` persists the choice across launches.
